45#ifndef ERR_H
46#define ERR_H
47
48#include <stdio.h>
49#include <stdarg.h>
50#include "srtp.h"
51
52#ifdef __cplusplus
53extern "C" {
54#endif
55
56/**
57 * @defgroup Error Error Codes
58 *
59 * Error status codes are represented by the enumeration srtp_err_status_t.
60 *
61 * @{
62 */
63
64/**
65 * @}
66 */
67
68typedef enum {
69 srtp_err_level_error,
70 srtp_err_level_warning,
71 srtp_err_level_info,
72 srtp_err_level_debug
73} srtp_err_reporting_level_t;
74
75/*
76 * err_reporting_init prepares the error system. If
77 * ERR_REPORTING_STDOUT is defined, it will log to stdout.
78 *
79 */
80
81srtp_err_status_t srtp_err_reporting_init(void);
82
83typedef void(srtp_err_report_handler_func_t)(srtp_err_reporting_level_t level,
84 const char *msg);
85
86srtp_err_status_t srtp_install_err_report_handler(
87 srtp_err_report_handler_func_t func);
88
89/*
90 * srtp_err_report reports a 'printf' formatted error
91 * string, followed by a an arg list. The level argument
92 * is one of srtp_err_reporting_level_t.
93 *
94 * Errors will be reported to stdout, if ERR_REPORTING_STDOUT
95 * is defined.
96 *
97 */
98
99void srtp_err_report(srtp_err_reporting_level_t level, const char *format, ...);
100
101/*
102 * debug_module_t defines a debug module
103 */
104
105typedef struct {
106 int on; /* 1 if debugging is on, 0 if it is off */
107 const char *name; /* printable name for debug module */
108} srtp_debug_module_t;
109
110#ifdef ENABLE_DEBUG_LOGGING
111
112#define debug_print0(mod, format) \
113 srtp_err_report(srtp_err_level_debug, ("%s: " format "\n"), mod.name)
114#define debug_print(mod, format, arg) \
115 srtp_err_report(srtp_err_level_debug, ("%s: " format "\n"), mod.name, arg)
116#define debug_print2(mod, format, arg1, arg2) \
117 srtp_err_report(srtp_err_level_debug, ("%s: " format "\n"), mod.name, \
118 arg1, arg2)
119
120#else
121
122#define debug_print0(mod, format) \
123 if (mod.on) \
124 srtp_err_report(srtp_err_level_debug, ("%s: " format "\n"), mod.name)
125#define debug_print(mod, format, arg) \
126 if (mod.on) \
127 srtp_err_report(srtp_err_level_debug, ("%s: " format "\n"), mod.name, arg)
128#define debug_print2(mod, format, arg1, arg2) \
129 if (mod.on) \
130 srtp_err_report(srtp_err_level_debug, ("%s: " format "\n"), mod.name, \
131 arg1, arg2)
132
133#endif
134
135#ifdef __cplusplus
136}
137#endif
138
139#endif /* ERR_H */
